{"award_age":46.0,"bio_image":"full\/545155e0a740cbfc94252b4949538ba9bd1628e2.jpg","category":"Physiology or Medicine","country":"Denmark","date_of_birth":"1874-11-15T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"1949-09-13T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/7\/7e\/August_Krogh_Bain_32006.jpg\/150px-August_Krogh_Bain_32006.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh","mini_bio":"<p><b>Schack August Steenberg Krogh<\/b> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Foreign_Member_of_the_Royal_Society\" title=\"Foreign Member of the Royal Society\" class=\"mw-redirect\">ForMemRS<\/a><\/span><sup id=\"cite_ref-frs_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-frs-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> (November 15, 1874 \u2013 September 13, 1949) was a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Denmark\" title=\"Denmark\">Danish<\/a> professor at the department of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Animal_physiology\" title=\"Animal physiology\" class=\"mw-redirect\">zoophysiology<\/a> at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Copenhagen\" title=\"University of Copenhagen\">University of Copenhagen<\/a> from 1916-1945.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He contributed a number of fundamental discoveries within several fields of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physiology\" title=\"Physiology\">physiology<\/a>, and is famous for developing the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Krogh_Principle\" title=\"Krogh Principle\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Krogh Principle<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>In 1920 August Krogh was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physiology_or_Medicine\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine\">Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine<\/a> for the discovery of the mechanism of regulation of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Capillary\" title=\"Capillary\">capillaries<\/a> in skeletal <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Muscle\" title=\"Muscle\">muscle<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/August_Krogh#cite_note-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Krogh was first to describe the adaptation of blood perfusion in muscle and other organs according to demands through opening and closing the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Arteriole\" title=\"Arteriole\">arterioles<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Capillary\" title=\"Capillary\">capillaries<\/a>.<\/p><p>Krogh was a pioneer in comparative studies on animals. He wrote his thesis on the respiration through the skin and lungs in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Frog\" title=\"Frog\">frogs<\/a>: <i>Respiratory Exchange of Animals<\/i>, 1915. Later Krogh took on studies of water and electrolyte homeostasis of aquatic animals and he published the books: <i>Osmotic Regulation<\/i> (1939) and <i>Comparative Physiology of Respiratory Mechanisms<\/i> (1941). In addition Krogh contributed more than 200 research articles in international journals. He was a constructor of scientific instruments of which several had considerable practical importance, <i>e.g.<\/i> the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Spirometer\" title=\"Spirometer\">spirometer<\/a> and the apparatus for measuring <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Basal_metabolic_rate\" title=\"Basal metabolic rate\">basal metabolic rate<\/a>.<\/p><p>Krogh brought insulin to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Denmark\" title=\"Denmark\">Denmark<\/a> shortly after its discovery in 1922 by <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nicolae_Paulescu\" title=\"Nicolae Paulescu\">Nicolae Paulescu<\/a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2011)\">citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> Together with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hans_Christian_Hagedorn\" title=\"Hans Christian Hagedorn\">Hagedorn<\/a>, Krogh made decisive contributions to establishing a Danish production of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Insulin\" title=\"Insulin\">insulin<\/a> by <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ethanol\" title=\"Ethanol\">ethanol<\/a> extraction of the hormone from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pancreas\" title=\"Pancreas\">pancreatic glands<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pig\" title=\"Pig\">pigs<\/a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2011)\">citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup><\/p><p>Much of Krogh's work was carried out in collaboration with his wife, <a href=\"\/w\/index.php?title=Marie_Krogh&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Marie Krogh (page does not exist)\">Marie Krogh<\/a> (1874\u20131943), a renowned scientist in her own right.<\/p><p>In 1910 August Krogh founded the first laboratory for animal <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physiology\" title=\"Physiology\">physiology<\/a> (zoophysiology) at the University of Copenhagen.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> It was located in a small townhouse in central Copenhagen (at Ny Vestergade 11). The laboratory was considerably enlarged in 1928, when it moved to a new building at Juliane Maries Vej 28-32 called The Rockefeller Complex (it was financed by the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rockefeller_Foundation\" title=\"Rockefeller Foundation\">Rockefeller Foundation<\/a>).<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> The building also gave place to the institutes of medical physiology and biophysics, and to the institute for the theory of gymnastics (exercise physiology). Today, the disciplines of animal physiology, exercise physiology, and some of the biochemical subdisciplines under the Faculty of Science are based at the August Krogh Institute, a building inaugurated in 1970.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> August and Marie had four children, the youngest of whom, Bodil, was born in 1918.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> Bodil married an eminent comparative physiologist, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Knut_Schmidt-Nielsen\" title=\"Knut Schmidt-Nielsen\">Knut Schmidt-Nielsen<\/a>, in 1939 and had three children.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> She received her Dental degree in 1941, was the first recipient of a Doctor in Odontology in 1946, and her PhD in 1955, all from the University of Copenhagen.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> Knut and Bodil moved to America and each had independently prominent physiology careers at prestigious institutions, including <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Duke_University\" title=\"Duke University\">Duke University<\/a> and Mount Desert Island Biological Laboratory, and were well known for their many students who became leaders in the field.<\/p><p><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Torkel_Weis-Fogh\" title=\"Torkel Weis-Fogh\">Torkel Weis-Fogh<\/a>, an eminent pioneer on the study of insect flight, was a student of August Krogh's.<\/p>","name":"August Krogh","place_of_birth":null,"place_of_death":null,"text":"August Krogh , Physiology or Medicine, 1920","year":1920.0}